Comparison¶

In the following notebook we're going to compare all the approaches we developed and test them on a small amount of professions that are grammatical ungendered and for which we have precise statics about. We will use both FastText's and Gonen's embeddings.

# gender direction

g_pca_01 = (sv[0]*pc[0]+sv[1]*pc[1])/(sv[0]+sv[1])/LA.norm((sv[0]*pc[0]+sv[1]*pc[1])/(sv[0]+sv[1]))

Step 2.3: pseudo-LDA¶

In [10]:
S_word = [['lei','lui'],
          ['donna','uomo'],
          ['madre','padre'],
          ['moglie','marito'],
          ['sorella','fratello'],
          ['femmina','maschio']]

G_word = db.read('gram_def_mf.txt', 'mf')
In [11]:
S_m_v = []
for w in S_word:
    S_m_v.append(E_ft.v(w[1]))
    
S_f_v = []
for w in S_word:
    S_f_v.append(E_ft.v(w[0]))
    
G_m_v = []
for w in G_word:
    G_m_v.append(E_ft.v(w[0]))
    
G_f_v = []
for w in G_word:
    G_f_v.append(E_ft.v(w[1]))

S_m = np.array(S_m_v).T
S_f = np.array(S_f_v).T
G_m = np.array(G_m_v).T
G_f = np.array(G_f_v).T
In [12]:
# delta semantic
Delta_S = np.dot(np.subtract(S_m, S_f), np.subtract(S_m, S_f).T)

# delta grammatical
Delta_G = np.dot(np.subtract(G_m, G_f), np.subtract(G_m, G_f).T)

# A
A = np.dot(np.linalg.inv(Delta_G), Delta_S)
In [13]:
# eigenvalues and eigenvectors
w, v = np.linalg.eig(A)

# gender direction: pick the eigenvector associated to the largest eigenvalue
g_e = v[:,np.argmax(w)] # already normalized

# delta semantic
Delta_S = np.dot(np.subtract(S_m, S_f), np.subtract(S_m, S_f).T)

# delta grammatical
Delta_G = np.dot(np.subtract(G_m, G_f), np.subtract(G_m, G_f).T)

# A
A = np.dot(np.linalg.inv(Delta_G), Delta_S)
